We recommended that Management require the concerned Heads of the following offices to take the following courses of action:
a. The Local Development Council and the MPDO, together with the concerned implementing offices, to re-evaluate the unimplemented PPAs to determine whether the expected outputs remain relevant and responsive to current needs of populace. Those considered as irrelevant and non-responsive be re-appropriated to enhance timely delivery of socio-economic and environmental services;
b. The concerned implementing offices to fast-track the completion of the projects that remain to be a priority concern to achieve the objectives of the PPAs; and
c. The MPDO enhance monitoring of the implementation of PPAs in coordination with the implementing offices and to submit regularly reports of implementation to the Municipal Mayor for his information so that appropriate measures can be instituted to obtain optimal utilization of funds;
Likewise, we recommended that Management direct the Local Finance Committee to appropriate the savings from previously implemented PPAs to new development projects that are aligned to the purpose of the fund.
